# Billing & Stripe

## Current repo state

- **No active implementation in-tree:** There is no `libs/monkey/`, no `app/api/webhook/stripe`, no `app/api/plan`, and no `getPlanContext` / `assertPlan` in this codebase.
- **Present:** `stripe` dependency and npm scripts (`stripe:listen` → `localhost:3002/api/webhook/stripe` when that route exists), plus **`libs/council/site.js`** (`stripe.freeTrial`, `stripe.plans` placeholder).

## When you add billing back

- Put tier definitions and provisioning logic in **`libs/council/`** (or a user-approved `libs/<pkg>/`), not a revived ad hoc `monkey` dump.
- Keep **webhook and plan API routes** thin: parse request → call library → return JSON.
- Document the flow in-repo (e.g. a short `docs/` note or comment block on the webhook route) once implemented; do not reference removed `docs/BILLING_ARCHITECTURE.md` paths.

## Avoid

- Copy-pasting old fork patterns (`subscriptionTiers.js`, `planContext.js`) unless those files exist again in the tree.
